President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Judy Shelton and Christopher Waller to key positions in his administration. Shelton is nominated to be a Member of the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System for the remainder of a 14-year term, while Waller is nominated for the same position for the remainder of a 14-year term expiring in 2030. Shelton has previously served as the United States Executive Director of the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, Chairman of the National Endowment for Democracy, and Vice Chairman of Empower America. Waller currently serves as the Executive Vice President and Director of Research at the Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis, and has held various academic positions in the field of economics. Both nominees have impressive educational backgrounds and experience in their respective fields.